  "prompt": "How much does an IFS officer get paid?",
  "response": "An IFS (Indian Foreign Service) officer's salary varies depending on their grade and years of service. Here's a general breakdown:\n\n1. Entry-level salary:\n- Basic pay starts around Rs. 50,000-60,000 per month\n- With various allowances, total monthly compensation can be Rs. 80,000-1,00,000\n\n2. Mid-career salary:\n- After 7-10 years of service, salary can range from Rs. 1-1.5 lakhs per month\n- Including allowances and benefits\n\n3. Senior-level salary:\n- Senior IFS officers can earn Rs. 2-3 lakhs per month\n- Additional diplomatic allowances and perks\n\n4. Additional benefits:\n- Free housing\n- Medical facilities\n- Foreign travel allowances\n- Diplomatic privileges\n- Pension and retirement benefits\n\nThe exact salary depends on:\n- Rank/grade\n- Years of service\n- Posting location\n- Additional responsibilities\n\nThese figures are approximate and subject to periodic revisions by the government. The salary structure follows the 7th Pay Commission recommendations.",
